Bhaskar Kamble¶

Berlin¶

12 December 2021¶

Topics Discussed¶

  1. Total Deaths.
  2. Deaths due to Covid.
  3. Excess Mortality in 2020 and 2021
  4. Deaths by Age Group in 2020 and 2021
  5. Excess Mortality and Covid Deaths in 2020 and 2021.

Two Key Observations:¶

  • In End-2020 beginning-2021 almost all the excess deaths are due to covid.

  • In End-2021 only a miniscule percent of excess deaths are due to covid.

Excess deaths in 2021¶

  • Only a miniscule percent were caused by covid.
  • Effects of lockdowns and social restriction? Old people are left alone, they die quickly?
  • Reduction in number of intensive care beds because of lack of health care workers?
  • Side effects of the vaccine?
  • Health personnel resigning due to mandatory vaccines for them?

Excess deaths in 2021¶

https://twitter.com/vonGammCom/status/1468889383596085252

Number of vaccines administered¶

Covid vaccinations and excess mortality: can there be a connection?¶

  • Issues with side effects such as myocarditis (https://www.ahajournals.org/doi/10.1161/circ.144.suppl_1.10712).
  • Charges of data falsification and failure to follow up side-effects in clinical trials of the Pfizer vaccine as conducted by Ventavia (https://www.bmj.com/content/bmj/375/bmj.n2635.full.pdf).

Summary¶

  • Excess mortality in 2020 was due to covid and occured in the age group above 60.
  • Mortality in the age group below 60 was practically unchanged compared to previous years.
  • Excess mortality in 2021 was not due to covid.
  • Peaks in the number of vaccines administered appear to correlate with excess mortality for 2021.
